      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sauté the mushrooms",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Set a large frying pan over a high heat with {{olive-oil}} of olive oil and {{butter-unsalted}} of butter. Once the butter foams, add {{chestnut-mushrooms}} of chestnut mushrooms in a single layer. Cook without stirring for 3 to 4 minutes until well browned, then toss and cook for 2 minutes more. Remove to a plate.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Build the sauce",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Reduce the heat to medium. Cook the shallots in the same pan for 3 minutes until soft. Add the garlic and thyme leaves for 1 minute, then add the chopped rehydrated porcini. Pour in {{dry-white-wine}} of white wine and stir to lift the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "fond",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp73oufn00009cv4qa4x39md"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " from the base. Add the strained porcini soaking liquor and simmer for 3 minutes until reduced by half. Return the chestnut mushrooms to the pan, add {{double-cream}} of cream, and cook for 2 minutes until the sauce thickens slightly. Season with salt and black pepper.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook and combine",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook {{tagliatelle-dried}} of tagliatelle in well-salted boiling water according to the packet. Reserve a ladle of pasta water, then drain. Add the tagliatelle to the sauce, tossing with tongs and adding a splash of pasta water if the sauce is thick. Remove from the heat. Scatter over the parsley and serve with grated Parmesan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
